h1. s:ifPermitted

h2. Purpose

Renders the body of the tag only if the user permissions are met.

This uses the underlying security provider to test the condition.

h2. Example

{docx:xml}
<s:ifPermitted role="ADMIN">
   Welcome admin!
</s:ifPermitted>
{docx}

h2. Attributes

{table}
*Name* | *Purpose*
role | Required - The role to test for. If the user has this role the body will be rendered
{table}

